44
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:49,900
We're jumping into the middle of a paragraph here.

45
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:52,220
We'll look at some other parts of this paragraph

46
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:55,300
in just a minute, but let's start at verse 22

47
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,180
and we'll read down through verse 25.

48
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:59,660
The Bible says this or reads this way,

49
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:01,540
but be you doers of the word

50
00:02:01,540 --> 00:02:05,940
and not hearers only deceiving your own selves.

51
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:08,220
For if any be a hearer of the word and not a doer,

52
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:10,660
he is likened to a man beholding his natural face

53
00:02:10,660 --> 00:02:15,020
in a glass for he beholdeth himself and goeth his way

54
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:19,100
and straightway forgetteth what manner of man he was.

55
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:22,860
But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty

56
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:26,259
and continueth therein, he being not a forgetful hearer,

57
00:02:26,259 --> 00:02:28,699
but a doer of the work,

58
00:02:28,699 --> 00:02:32,539
this man shall be blessed in his deed.

59
00:02:32,539 --> 00:02:33,860
You know, it's a classic story

60
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:35,940
that many of us are familiar with.

61
00:02:35,940 --> 00:02:39,539
I don't know when you maybe first heard or saw this story,

62
00:02:39,539 --> 00:02:43,419
but it's a story that has some basic elements in it

63
00:02:43,419 --> 00:02:48,179
that still remain in some of the fairy tale stories

64
00:02:48,179 --> 00:02:51,100
and things that we grew up with as children.

65
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,100
There is a particular story that comes to mind

66
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,539
or came to mind when I was reading

67
00:02:56,539 --> 00:02:58,380
through this passage of scripture.

68
00:02:58,380 --> 00:03:01,580
This story contains a wicked queen.

69
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:06,460
It contains a poisoned apple, seven dwarfs,

70
00:03:06,460 --> 00:03:09,660
a glass coffin, a handsome prince,

71
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:14,660
and of course, the classic, they lived happily ever after.

72
00:03:14,899 --> 00:03:17,360
If you're familiar with the story that I'm talking about,

73
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,839
this beloved fairy tale, which has these elements,

74
00:03:19,839 --> 00:03:23,080
is known as Snow White.

75
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:26,720
And you know, as you consider the history

76
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,660
of the background of Snow White,

77
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:32,880
Snow White was actually a story that was published

78
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,539
all the way back in 1812 in a book

79
00:03:35,539 --> 00:03:38,360
called Grimm's Book of Fairy Tales.

80
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,440
The brothers Grimm would continue to improve the story

81
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:46,320
until they had their final revision that came out in 1854.

82
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:49,919
Years later, it would be put into an animated movie

83
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:52,320
with music and things like that.

84
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:54,639
But as you go throughout that story,

85
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:57,399
one of the things that appears in that story

86
00:03:57,399 --> 00:04:01,399
is that you have a queen who comes before a mirror

87
00:04:01,399 --> 00:04:04,479
and she asks this question.

88
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:06,600
Mirror, mirror on the wall,

89
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:09,800
who is the fairest of them all?

90
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,899
And you know, when the queen comes before the mirror,

91
00:04:11,899 --> 00:04:15,720
for quite some time, she is very content

92
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:19,000
to hear the answer and to see the result

93
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,600
or hear the result that the mirror gives to her.

94
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:25,040
You are the fairest in all of the land.

95
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:28,140
But then there comes a day

96
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:30,119
when the queen comes before the mirror

97
00:04:30,119 --> 00:04:32,880
and she asks mirror, mirror on the wall,

98
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,920
who is the fairest of them all?

99
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:37,279
And the mirror finally tells her

100
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:40,200
that there is someone who is fairer,

101
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,640
someone who is more beautiful,

102
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:45,279
someone who has taken her place.

103
00:04:45,279 --> 00:04:48,839
And the queen's response is very telling.

104
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:51,399
All is fine as long as the mirror is saying,

105
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:53,559
hey, everything is great, you're the fairest.

106
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:56,519
But when the mirror finally reveals

107
00:04:56,519 --> 00:04:59,519
that there is something about her

108
00:04:59,519 --> 00:05:01,380
that she didn't want to hear,

109
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:05,040
she has a completely different response.

110
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:08,720
So we come to this passage of scripture in James 1.

111
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,859
James is not speaking in fairy tales,

112
00:05:10,859 --> 00:05:13,760
but he does use an illustration of a mirror

113
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,359
here in this passage of scripture

114
00:05:15,359 --> 00:05:18,239
to teach us spiritual truth.

115
00:05:18,239 --> 00:05:21,559
He likens the word of God as to a mirror.

116
00:05:21,559 --> 00:05:25,279
And in so doing so, he teaches the importance

117
00:05:25,279 --> 00:05:30,019
that the mirror ought to have in every one of our lives.

118
00:05:30,019 --> 00:05:33,320
Not the physical mirror, but the mirror of God's word.

119
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,959
And so I want us to notice this morning

120
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,260
three important aspects of this,

121
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:39,119
what for many of us is probably

122
00:05:39,119 --> 00:05:41,119
a familiar passage of scripture,

123
00:05:41,119 --> 00:05:43,600
but I wanna break it down into three different aspects.

124
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,959
And I want us to consider this morning,

125
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:50,959
what is our response to the mirror of God's word?

126
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:53,640
How do you respond to the mirror of God's word?

127
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:56,799
Well, as we come to this passage of scripture in verse 22,

128
00:05:56,799 --> 00:05:59,000
we see that God's word gives to us,

129
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,480
first of all, some instruction.

130
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:06,480
He gives us some very clear instruction in verse 22.

131
00:06:06,779 --> 00:06:09,880
I mentioned that we are in the middle of a paragraph here

132
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:12,119
in verses 22 through 25.

133
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,279
And in order to be able to get the whole feel

134
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,720
of what is taking place,

135
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:18,739
we're gonna back up to verse 19.

136
00:06:18,739 --> 00:06:21,200
In verse 19, the scripture reads this way.

137
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,320
Wherefore, my beloved brethren,

138
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:25,679
let every man be swift to hear,

139
00:06:25,679 --> 00:06:28,920
slow to speak, slow to wrath.

140
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,059
You know, when you're working with children,

141
00:06:31,059 --> 00:06:33,239
it is often best to keep instructions

142
00:06:33,239 --> 00:06:36,720
brief, short, and simple.

143
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,119
As we come to this verse,

144
00:06:38,119 --> 00:06:41,040
John is, or excuse me, James is sharing a truth

145
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:44,200
and he keeps it short and sweet, if you will.

146
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,959
He uses this phrase, he says,

147
00:06:45,959 --> 00:06:49,519
but be ye doers of the word

148
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:53,119
and not hearers only in verse 22.

149
00:06:53,119 --> 00:06:56,200
But he's referencing back to what he's talked about here

150
00:06:56,200 --> 00:07:01,200
in verse 19, where he says that we need to be swift to hear,

151
00:07:01,799 --> 00:07:05,679
slow to speak, slow to wrath.

152
00:07:05,679 --> 00:07:07,160
You know, the word of God ought to play

153
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,440
a very important part of our lives.

154
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,799
The word of God ought to have a preeminence

155
00:07:11,799 --> 00:07:13,079
that is there in our lives.

156
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:16,160
And here in these verses, in verses 19,

157
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,760
even down through verse 20 and 21,

158
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,519
he gives to us some instruction.

159
00:07:20,519 --> 00:07:23,640
Now, we don't have the time to unpack each of these verses,

160
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:25,279
but I want us to consider something here

161
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:27,839
specifically in verse 19.

162
00:07:27,839 --> 00:07:30,619
He gives us these short, simple instructions.

163
00:07:30,619 --> 00:07:33,959
First of all, he says we are to be swift to hear.

164
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:36,019
The idea there is that there ought to be a delight

165
00:07:36,019 --> 00:07:37,519
and a hunger for God's word.

166
00:07:37,839 --> 00:07:39,359
And it's the picture of a person

167
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:44,359
who has their ears wide open while their mouth is closed.

168
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,720
You know, at camp, some of your young people

169
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,279
came to camp this week and we do at camp,

170
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:52,880
we teach them this at the very beginning orientation,

171
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:55,799
we teach them what we call the eyeballs click system.

172
00:07:55,799 --> 00:07:59,079
And campers, where were you?

173
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,260
You didn't help me here.

174
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:03,079
I'm gonna go back a couple of seconds and repeat that, okay?

175
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:05,359
And so at camp, when they come to orientation,

176
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:08,880
we do what we call the eyeballs click system, okay?

177
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:10,559
And basically the system works this way

178
00:08:10,559 --> 00:08:12,720
for those of you who are adults and have never been there.

179
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,200
Anytime that myself or Mr. Kelly

180
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,779
or someone is giving announcements,

181
00:08:16,779 --> 00:08:20,239
if they say the word eyeballs, two of them are still awake,

182
00:08:20,239 --> 00:08:22,160
okay, the campers should say click.

183
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,880
And I tell them on Monday,

184
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:26,160
there are a couple of things that need to take place

185
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,760
when you say click.

186
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,239
And what needs to happen is this,

187
00:08:29,239 --> 00:08:32,000
as soon as you say click, your mouth needs to go closed,

188
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,700
your eyes need to look in the direction

189
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:34,900
of the one who is speaking

190
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,739
and your ears need to go wide open.

191
00:08:37,739 --> 00:08:39,979
Have you ever noticed it's hard to listen to someone

192
00:08:39,979 --> 00:08:40,979
when you're talking?

193
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,619
It's really hard to listen to someone

194
00:08:44,619 --> 00:08:46,619
when the sound of our own voice

195
00:08:46,619 --> 00:08:48,419
is really what we want to hear.

196
00:08:48,419 --> 00:08:50,599
And in this passage of scripture,

197
00:08:50,599 --> 00:08:53,059
God teaches us a very valuable lesson

198
00:08:53,059 --> 00:08:56,859
well before he ever gets to the fact that we need to,

199
00:08:56,859 --> 00:08:59,000
when we come before the mirror of God's word,

200
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,380
allow it to affect our lives.

201
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:02,099
He says, you wanna know one of the best ways

202
00:09:02,099 --> 00:09:05,219
that you can allow God's word to affect your lives?

203
00:09:05,219 --> 00:09:07,659
Is just simply be willing to listen.

204
00:09:07,659 --> 00:09:12,380
Be swift, be desiring to hear what God wants to say to you.

205
00:09:12,380 --> 00:09:14,380
And in order for that to happen,

206
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:19,239
we have to be quick to hear, slow to speak

207
00:09:19,239 --> 00:09:24,239
and even consider our response being slow to wrath.

208
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:28,140
James would go on in these next few verses

209
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:31,039
and he would talk about as God's word does a work

210
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:33,640
in our hearts, according to verse 22,

211
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:36,760
that God's word does a work in our, excuse me, verse 20.

212
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:40,719
He says then that we need to lay apart all filthiness

213
00:09:40,719 --> 00:09:43,479
and superfluity of naughtiness

214
00:09:43,479 --> 00:09:45,880
or the abundance of naughtiness in our lives.

215
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,840
And instead, what we ought to do

216
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:51,880
is we ought to receive with meekness the engrafted word

217
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:55,599
which is able to save your souls.

218
00:09:55,599 --> 00:09:58,520
Our response ought to be that I wanna be swift to hear

219
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,479
God speak to me.

220
00:09:59,479 --> 00:10:00,320
My desire.

221
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:04,800
is to hear from God, and I want that engrafted word

222
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,460
which is able to save my soul.

223
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:09,400
I want it to affect my life.

224
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,640
Hey, is that your attitude when you come to God's word?

225
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,980
When your pastor preaches,

226
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:16,040
when the Sunday school teacher begins the lesson,

227
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:18,840
when you have your personal devotions in God's word,

228
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,140
do you come before God and say,

229
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:22,940
God, all ears speak to me?

230
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:26,860
Or do we come to God's word with our opinion,

231
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:31,920
with our thoughts and our desires and our feelings?

232
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:35,760
If the word of God is going to be able to have effect

233
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:39,160
on our lives, we must be willing to come to God's word

234
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:42,280
and allow it to change and affect our lives.

235
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,920
And that means that we must be willing

236
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:47,360
to resign our thoughts, to quiet our hearts

237
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,080
and come before God's word.

238
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:52,360
And the instruction is that we would not just be a hearer

239
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:56,000
of the word, but allow it to influence our lives so much

240
00:10:56,020 --> 00:11:00,020
that we choose to do what we learn in God's word.

241
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:02,860
This is not the only place that God's word references

242
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:05,220
this idea of being a doer of the word.

243
00:11:05,220 --> 00:11:08,060
In fact, God's word gives us multiple admonitions

244
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:11,300
to be a doer of the word.

245
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:14,380
One of those famous passages is in Matthew chapter seven

246
00:11:14,380 --> 00:11:16,280
at the end of the Sermon on the Mount.

247
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,920
Jesus has been speaking, he's given the beatitudes,

248
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:21,780
he's confronted some false teachings and some false prophets

249
00:11:21,780 --> 00:11:23,900
and as he gets to the end of chapter seven,

250
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,940
he closes with an illustration

251
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,640
and you're familiar with this illustration

252
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,440
though you may not know where it is in the Bible.

253
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:32,120
Many of you are probably familiar with this illustration.

254
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,720
It's a story about the wise man and the foolish man

255
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,860
who were building their houses.

256
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:37,640
We could sing the Sunday school song this morning,

257
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,920
but we won't take the time to do that.

258
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:42,100
But we know that through that story,

259
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:46,960
there is a wise man who builds his house on the rock.

260
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:50,120
Yeah, and all of a sudden the wind begins to blow,

261
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,760
the rain comes down, the flood beats upon that house

262
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:56,100
and because he dug and the Bible says

263
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:58,400
in another passage of scripture, I believe it's in Luke,

264
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,300
it says he dug deep and he had a solid foundation.

265
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:04,420
When all of that happened, his house stood.

266
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:06,300
But then there's this other person

267
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:09,540
who builds his house on the sand.

268
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:12,180
Doesn't have a very solid foundation.

269
00:12:12,180 --> 00:12:14,980
And when the wind begins to come, the rains begin to fall,

270
00:12:14,980 --> 00:12:16,700
the floods begin to beat on that house,

271
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:20,980
Jesus describes the result of that as it fell and great.

272
00:12:20,980 --> 00:12:23,240
It was utter catastrophe.

273
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,960
You realize the difference between the wise man

274
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,800
and the foolish man?

275
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,400
We often talk about the foundation,

276
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,680
but you know what the foundation is?

277
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,600
The foundation there, the difference is

278
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:37,180
that there is someone who hears God's word and does it,

279
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:39,280
that's the wise man.

280
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:44,280
The foolish man is the person who hears but refuses to do.

281
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,200
That's the difference.

282
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:49,040
There are people who hear God's truth all the time

283
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,880
and they wonder why don't I have God's blessing

284
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:52,500
in my life?

285
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:53,780
The problem is you're hearing God's word,

286
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:57,340
but you're choosing not to do God's word.

287
00:12:57,340 --> 00:13:00,220
And so the instruction that James follows up with here

288
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:02,580
in this passage of scripture at the very beginning

289
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:04,340
of his letter or not very far into it,

290
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:08,340
he says this, be a doer of the word and not just a hearer.

291
00:13:08,340 --> 00:13:10,580
James is gonna come back to this idea

292
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:13,460
in James chapter four and verse 17 when he says this,

293
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:16,740
therefore to him that knoweth to do good.

294
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:17,660
How do you know it's good?

295
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:19,620
Well, you heard it at some point in time.

296
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:21,040
You've seen it in God's word.

297
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,800
God has shared with you what the good

298
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,120
or the right thing is to do.

299
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:27,800
Therefore to him that knoweth to do good

300
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:32,800
and doeth it not, to him it is sin.

301
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,200
This is where the mirror begins to point out some things

302
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,960
in our lives that we don't like to hear

303
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,560
and we start getting angry at the mirror.

304
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:44,240
Have you ever stepped in front of the mirror

305
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,720
and you didn't like what you saw?

306
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:50,300
Hair out of place, maybe some drool from the morning,

307
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,860
maybe you brushed your teeth and you didn't know,

308
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,540
you know, you had a little bit on the side of your face

309
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:55,380
and so your spouse points it out to you

310
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:57,420
or maybe, you know, a kid points it out to you

311
00:13:57,420 --> 00:13:59,580
or something but you come before the mirror

312
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:02,660
and you see something there that you don't like.

313
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:05,460
Do you punch the mirror every time that happens?

314
00:14:05,460 --> 00:14:06,980
Probably not.

315
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:08,860
If you do, you have a pretty expensive

316
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,060
mirror budget somewhere.

317
00:14:11,820 --> 00:14:13,020
What do we do?

318
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:15,980
We take what the mirror reveals about us

319
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,200
and if we don't like it, we probably change

320
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,320
something about it.

321
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:23,119
We go and we wash it off, we comb our hair,

322
00:14:23,119 --> 00:14:24,740
we do these things, why?

323
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:27,320
Because what the mirror reveals to us

324
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:30,399
isn't what we want to see.

325
00:14:31,279 --> 00:14:33,559
Someone who's gonna be a doer of the word

326
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:37,679
is someone who has a desire to come before the mirror

327
00:14:37,679 --> 00:14:41,040
of God's word and say, God, I want you to show me

328
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,800
truth from your word.

329
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:45,600
And so our purpose, when we come before God's word

330
00:14:46,179 --> 00:14:48,460
is to hear it and it ought to be that we would

331
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:53,220
just not hear it but that we would be a doer of the word.

332
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:56,380
And so the instruction here really can't get any clearer.

333
00:14:56,380 --> 00:14:58,899
Do what God's word says.

334
00:14:58,899 --> 00:15:00,700
That then ought to cause us to step back

335
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:05,179
and ask this question, am I doing what God's word says?

336
00:15:05,179 --> 00:15:08,820
Am I someone who is a hearer of the word

337
00:15:08,820 --> 00:15:10,899
but not a doer of the word?

338
00:15:10,899 --> 00:15:12,640
Perhaps we ought to ask it this way,

339
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:17,640
in what area of my life am I not doing God's word

340
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:19,740
and the truth that I've heard

341
00:15:19,740 --> 00:15:22,279
or I know I ought to be doing in God's word?

342
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:25,660
And so as we come to this passage of scripture,

343
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:28,559
James says and uses the illustration of a mirror,

344
00:15:28,559 --> 00:15:30,140
we're gonna get to that here in just a minute,

345
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:33,500
but he says, before we ever address that illustration,

346
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,420
you need to know God's expectation is this,

347
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:38,740
be a doer of the word.

348
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:41,960
God wants us to respond properly to his word.

349
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,540
Then there's a second aspect of this passage

350
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:47,940
that we're gonna look at in verses 23 through 25,

351
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:49,460
where we not only see the instruction,

352
00:15:49,460 --> 00:15:52,779
be a doer of the word and not a hearer only.

353
00:15:52,779 --> 00:15:55,140
And then he goes into this illustration

354
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:57,260
in verses 23 through 25.

355
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:59,559
Now we read down through this illustration.

356
00:15:59,559 --> 00:16:02,300
We won't take the time to read this passage again,

357
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:04,100
but as he gives us this illustration,

358
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:06,300
basically James says this, James says,

359
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,839
I'm gonna present to you two different people.

360
00:16:08,839 --> 00:16:11,520
Let's talk about exhibit A.

361
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:14,700
Exhibit A is the person who comes before the mirror

362
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:17,380
and we're just going to simply identify this person

363
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:19,179
as the looker.

364
00:16:19,179 --> 00:16:20,339
This is the person who,

365
00:16:20,339 --> 00:16:22,460
when they come before the mirror of God's word,

366
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:25,520
they're willing to look into the mirror,

367
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:28,860
see what God's word says, even hear it,

368
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:33,860
but then they go away and they forget what God's word says.

369
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,100
There's an interesting word in verse 22

370
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,300
and it's the verse 23, excuse me.

371
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:43,480
It says this, beholding his natural face in a glass.

372
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,080
The word beholding there is this,

373
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:49,559
it means to perceive clearly, to understand.

374
00:16:49,559 --> 00:16:51,640
In other words, this person is presented

375
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,000
with the truth of God's word,

376
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,880
whether it's in reading God's word,

377
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,240
hearing God's word preached,

378
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,839
it could be done through godly music

379
00:16:57,839 --> 00:16:59,860
that conveys the truth of God's word,

380
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:01,720
but somehow they hear God's word

381
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,760
and it isn't that they don't understand it.

382
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:07,619
It isn't that it's too high for them to understand.

383
00:17:07,619 --> 00:17:09,240
God's word has been made clear.

384
00:17:10,179 --> 00:17:11,000
It's been explained to them.

385
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,880
It's been made evident to them what needs to happen,

386
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:18,380
but they are just willing to look.

387
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:21,059
And then they purposefully go away

388
00:17:21,059 --> 00:17:25,020
and they forget what manner of man they were.

389
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:27,339
The word forget there is the idea of neglect.

390
00:17:27,339 --> 00:17:30,020
You ever forgotten something, forgotten keys?

391
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:33,260
Maybe you've forgotten your wallet or your purse somewhere.

392
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,779
Maybe you've forgotten something

393
00:17:34,779 --> 00:17:36,220
even more important than that.

394
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:38,380
Maybe you've forgotten your child somewhere.

395
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:42,059
And you know, when something is important to you,

396
00:17:42,059 --> 00:17:44,619
you try not to forget it, right?

397
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:48,140
Well, here he says for the looker,

398
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:50,420
the things that he's learned, read,

399
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:52,500
heard from God's word and knows he ought to put

400
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,540
into practice in his life,

401
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:57,179
the one who is the looker, exhibit A,

402
00:17:57,179 --> 00:17:59,700
the one who ultimately when the storms arise,

403
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:02,860
the floods come, their life is gonna be a disaster,

404
00:18:02,860 --> 00:18:06,580
they neglect, they forget.

405
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:09,440
They make really a choice

406
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,679
not to apply God's word to their life.

407
00:18:11,679 --> 00:18:12,520
Why?

408
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,920
Because they're just simply a looker.

409
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,080
They're even willing to look into God's word

410
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:18,240
and find information to help other people.

411
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,160
They're willing to look into God's word

412
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:23,399
to hopefully find some sort of a life vest

413
00:18:23,399 --> 00:18:24,899
that when trouble comes into their life,

414
00:18:24,899 --> 00:18:26,520
they can maybe use God's word that way.

415
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:29,640
But to allow God's word to affect their daily life,

416
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:34,640
they're just a looker and not choosing to be a doer.

417
00:18:35,100 --> 00:18:36,820
That's exhibit A.

418
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:40,140
Exhibit B, as we continue to go on in these verses then,

419
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:43,260
we see that there is something that is different.

420
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:48,260
We don't see this one who is exhibit A

421
00:18:48,580 --> 00:18:50,440
not being exposed to God's word.

422
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,619
They've heard God's word.

423
00:18:51,619 --> 00:18:53,080
They've heard truth presented.

424
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:54,840
That's not what really makes the difference.

425
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:58,340
The difference is exhibit B is someone

426
00:18:58,340 --> 00:19:00,299
who hears the word of God,

427
00:19:00,299 --> 00:19:02,859
comes before the mirror of God's word

428
00:19:02,859 --> 00:19:04,400
and their choice is this.

429
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,380
I don't wanna neglect this.

430
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:09,739
I don't want this to just come in one ear and out the other.

431
00:19:09,739 --> 00:19:12,179
I want to have God's blessing on my life.

432
00:19:12,179 --> 00:19:15,220
So I'm going to choose to be a hearer of the word

433
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:19,100
and a doer of the word.

434
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,619
If we look at these two different people,

435
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:23,979
we classified exhibit A as the looker.

436
00:19:23,979 --> 00:19:26,380
Exhibit B this morning,

437
00:19:26,380 --> 00:19:28,820
I would classify him as this kind of a person.

438
00:19:28,820 --> 00:19:31,020
He is a lingerer.

439
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,100
He is a lingerer.

440
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:34,200
Notice the word as we read down

441
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:37,200
through this passage of scripture in verse 25,

442
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:39,960
it says, but who so looketh into the perfect law of liberty

443
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:43,440
and continueth therein.

444
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:46,960
My mind goes to that person who is lingering,

445
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:49,359
who is continuing,

446
00:19:49,359 --> 00:19:51,400
who is seeking to stay with

447
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:54,919
or stand near something as long as they can.

448
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:59,960
And if they can't stay by that any longer,

449
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:00,799
then they can't.

450
00:20:00,799 --> 00:20:03,799
They carry the thought, they carry the concept,

451
00:20:03,799 --> 00:20:06,079
they carry the memory in their mind,

452
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,999
they take it with them.

453
00:20:09,939 --> 00:20:12,719
I mentioned that half of our family

454
00:20:12,719 --> 00:20:14,879
is not with us this morning.

455
00:20:14,879 --> 00:20:17,379
But you know, there are different ways

456
00:20:17,379 --> 00:20:20,019
that we can stay in touch.

457
00:20:20,019 --> 00:20:22,019
There are different ways that we can think

458
00:20:22,019 --> 00:20:24,659
about our children, and even though we may be

459
00:20:24,659 --> 00:20:27,219
hundreds of miles apart,

460
00:20:27,219 --> 00:20:29,199
we can still have the thought of them.

461
00:20:29,199 --> 00:20:30,899
It's not like they're completely gone,

462
00:20:30,899 --> 00:20:32,499
that they've disappeared, that we don't want

463
00:20:32,499 --> 00:20:33,799
anything to do with them.

464
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:35,499
You wanna know something, we go around the campsite

465
00:20:35,499 --> 00:20:37,199
and there are memories that begin to flash

466
00:20:37,199 --> 00:20:39,139
into our minds all of the time,

467
00:20:39,139 --> 00:20:40,779
of the things that our children have done

468
00:20:40,779 --> 00:20:42,279
as they've grown up there at camp,

469
00:20:42,279 --> 00:20:43,939
and we see them there, why?

470
00:20:43,939 --> 00:20:47,279
Because the memory, the importance,

471
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:51,459
it's significant to us, and it lingers in our mind.

472
00:20:53,859 --> 00:20:56,399
Hey, can I ask you this question this morning?

473
00:20:56,419 --> 00:20:59,359
What is your habit when you hear God's word?

474
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:01,359
Do you come into God's word and you walk out

475
00:21:01,359 --> 00:21:06,179
these doors and God's word is forgotten?

476
00:21:06,179 --> 00:21:08,639
Kelly will often encourage the young people

477
00:21:08,639 --> 00:21:10,479
before they leave to not let the gates

478
00:21:10,479 --> 00:21:13,279
at the end of the road as they go out,

479
00:21:13,279 --> 00:21:15,939
which is actually the entrance when they come in, okay,

480
00:21:15,939 --> 00:21:18,479
that when they go out the front gate,

481
00:21:18,479 --> 00:21:20,719
to don't let them be like giant erasers

482
00:21:20,719 --> 00:21:22,479
where everything that they've heard at camp this week

483
00:21:22,479 --> 00:21:24,319
from God's word and they learn in their devotions

484
00:21:24,319 --> 00:21:25,959
from their counselors, from the preaching,

485
00:21:26,779 --> 00:21:28,759
from the instruction, don't let it be like a magic eraser

486
00:21:28,759 --> 00:21:30,779
that all of a sudden when you go out that gate,

487
00:21:30,779 --> 00:21:32,259
that whew, it's gone.

488
00:21:33,619 --> 00:21:35,559
Take the truth with you.

489
00:21:36,699 --> 00:21:40,299
Are these doors like mental erasers,

490
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:41,859
spiritual erasers to you?

491
00:21:42,799 --> 00:21:46,339
I've heard God's word, now I've gotta get back to life,

492
00:21:46,339 --> 00:21:48,639
and you don't take God's word with you?

493
00:21:48,639 --> 00:21:52,279
Or do you allow God's word to linger in your heart?

494
00:21:52,279 --> 00:21:53,579
Can I give you a food illustration?

495
00:21:53,579 --> 00:21:55,079
It's the idea of a marinade.

496
00:21:55,979 --> 00:21:57,379
What do you do with a marinade?

497
00:21:57,379 --> 00:21:59,759
You don't just pop it into a bag for five seconds,

498
00:21:59,759 --> 00:22:01,159
take it back out, right?

499
00:22:01,159 --> 00:22:04,219
If you really want that flavor to get into the meat,

500
00:22:04,219 --> 00:22:06,259
you have to let it sit in there for a while

501
00:22:06,259 --> 00:22:09,699
so that it begins to soak it up, it begins to permeate it.

502
00:22:11,339 --> 00:22:13,499
Do you let God's word linger in your heart?

503
00:22:14,899 --> 00:22:16,339
Do you let God's word begin to get in

504
00:22:16,339 --> 00:22:18,879
and permeate your life, or do we respond

505
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:23,179
like the wicked witch in the Grimm's fairy tales

506
00:22:23,179 --> 00:22:25,519
that when it tells us something we don't like to hear,

507
00:22:26,379 --> 00:22:28,739
automatically we get shut off to God's word?

508
00:22:28,739 --> 00:22:30,979
God, you can't penetrate that area of my life.

509
00:22:30,979 --> 00:22:34,919
No, sir, you can't tell me how to thank God.

510
00:22:34,919 --> 00:22:36,419
Say, does God really tell me how to thank?

511
00:22:36,419 --> 00:22:38,679
Read Philippians chapter four in verse eight.

512
00:22:38,679 --> 00:22:40,819
Whatsoever things are true, honest, just, pure, lovely,

513
00:22:40,819 --> 00:22:42,119
if there's virtue, if there's any praise,

514
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:43,919
think on these things, God says.

515
00:22:43,919 --> 00:22:46,299
Here's what you ought to be thinking.

516
00:22:46,299 --> 00:22:48,599
So God's word addresses the areas of our lives,

